## Variants

Variants are **semantic**, not purely visual. They map to intent:

- `primary` – high-emphasis, single best next action on a surface
- `secondary` – supporting actions that are still important
- `ghost` – low-emphasis actions, often inline or tertiary options

<Canvas>
  <Story id="components-button--variants" of={ButtonStories.Primary} />
</Canvas>

> **Guideline:** Avoid having more than one `primary` Button per view. If
> everything is emphasized, nothing is.

---

## Sizes

Button size is driven by layout density and input method:

- `sm` – dense UIs, tables, secondary actions
- `md` – default for desktop product surfaces
- `lg` – high-emphasis actions, mobile-first contexts

Text remains relatively small and neutral; padding establishes the touch target.

